name: Rice
description: In Nepali society, rice is referred to as 'bhat' and holds a central place in daily life and cultural practices. It is the food for most Nepalese and is consumed at almost every meal.

name: Dal
description: Dal is a vital component of the daily diet, typically paired with rice to form the classic dish 'dal bhat'.

name: Cauliflower
description: Cauliflower, referred to as 'kauli' in Nepali, is a popular and versatile commonly used vegetable.

name: Potato
description: Potato, referred to as 'alu' in Nepali, is a highly valued and widely consumed vegetable.

name: Cabbage
description: Cabbage is appreciated for its nutritional benefits, providing vitamins, minerals, and fiber.

name: Peas
description: Peas, referred to as 'kerau' in Nepali, are a popular and nutritious vegetable.

name: Green Bean
description: Green beans, referred to as 'simi' in Nepali, are a widely consumed and cherished vegetable.

name: Brinjal
description: Brinjal is appreciated for its nutritional benefits, providing vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants.

name: Bitter Gourd
description: Bitter Gourd, referred to as 'tite karela' in Nepali, is a valued vegetable known for its distinct bitter flavor and numerous health benefits.

name: Chickpea
description: Chickpeas, referred to as 'chana' in Nepali, are valued for their high nutritional content, including protein, fiber, vitamins, and minerals.

name: Tomato
description: Tomatoes are an essential ingredient in various dishes, including curries, chutneys, salads, and soups.

name: Boiled Egg
description: Eggs play a crucial role in the diet of many Nepalese, providing a vital source of nutrition.

name: Chicken
description: Chicken is valued for its lean protein content and versatility in cooking, allowing for a wide range of flavors and textures.

name: Mutton
description: Mutton is valued for its nutritional content, including protein and essential vitamins.

name: Pork
description: Pork is appreciated for its rich flavor and versatility in cooking.

name: Apple
description: Apples are known for their crisp texture, sweet-tart flavor, and nutritional benefits, including being a good source of fiber, vitamins, and antioxidants.

name: Banana
description: Bananas are a rich source of potassium, vitamins, and fiber, making them a healthy snack choice.

name: Fried Egg
description: Fried eggs are appreciated for their protein content and are a satisfying and nutritious addition to any meal.

name: Veg ChowMein
description: Chow Mein is a popular dish in Nepali society, known for its flavorful combination of stir-fried noodles and mixed vegetables.

name: Chicken ChowMein
description: Chow Mein is a beloved dish in Nepali cuisine, featuring stir-fried noodles combined with a flavorful mix of vegetables, meats, and sometimes seafood.

name: Pork ChowMein
description: Chow Mein is a beloved dish in Nepali cuisine, featuring stir-fried noodles combined with a flavorful mix of vegetables, meats, and sometimes seafood.

name: Buffalo Meat
description: Buffalo meat is also valued for its nutritional benefits, providing essential vitamins, minerals, and protein.

name: Buff ChowMein
description: Chow Mein is a beloved dish in Nepali cuisine, featuring stir-fried noodles combined with a flavorful mix of vegetables, meats, and sometimes seafood.

name: Chicken Momo
description: Momo is a cherished and iconic dish consisting of dumplings filled with a savory mixture of minced meat, vegetables, and spices.

name: Veg Momo
description: Momo is a cherished and iconic dish consisting of dumplings filled with a savory mixture of minced meat, vegetables, and spices.

name: Buff Momo
description: Momo is a cherished and iconic dish consisting of dumplings filled with a savory mixture of minced meat, vegetables, and spices.

name: Chicken Pizza
description: Pizza typically features a round, flatbread base topped with tomato sauce, cheese, and a variety of toppings, which can include vegetables, meats, and herbs.

name: Mushroom Pizza
description: Pizza typically features a round, flatbread base topped with tomato sauce, cheese, and a variety of toppings, which can include vegetables, meats, and herbs.

name: Cow Milk
description: Nutritious dairy beverage with a balanced mix of protein, fats, and carbohydrates.

name: Buffalo Milk
description: Rich and creamy milk from buffalo, higher in fat content compared to cow milk.

name: Mango Juice
description: Sweet and tropical fruit juice made from ripe mangoes.

name: Orange Juice
description: Citrus fruit juice with a tangy and refreshing taste, rich in vitamin C.

name: Apple Juice
description: Sweet and crisp fruit juice made from fresh apples.

name: Pineapple Juice
description: Tropical fruit juice with a sweet and tangy flavor, made from fresh pineapples.

name: Sel Roti
description: A traditional homemade, sweet, ring-shaped rice bread/doughnut prepared during the festivals of Dashain and Tihar.

name: Thukpa
description: A noodle soup that originated in Tibet and is popular in Nepal, often made with meat, vegetables, and a flavorful broth.

name: Gundruk
description: Fermented leafy green vegetable, often used as a side dish or in soups and curries.

name: Sukuti
description: Dried meat, typically buffalo, which is marinated with spices and then sun-dried, often served as a snack or with beaten rice.

name: Yomari
description: A traditional Newari dessert made from rice flour dough shaped like a fish, filled with sweetened sesame seeds or molasses.

name: Kwati
description: A mixed bean soup, traditionally consumed during the festival of Janai Purnima, made with a variety of beans and flavored with spices.

name: Bara
description: A traditional Newari snack made from lentil batter, often fried and served with chutney or curry.

name: Chatamari
description: Often referred to as Nepali pizza, this is a traditional Newari dish made from rice flour batter and topped with meat, vegetables, and spices.

name: Juju Dhau
description: Known as the 'king of curds,' this is a rich and creamy yogurt made in the town of Bhaktapur.

name: Kheer
description: A rice pudding made with milk, sugar, and cardamom, often garnished with nuts and raisins.

name: Bhatmas Sandeko
description: A spicy and tangy salad made from roasted soybeans mixed with onions, tomatoes, and spices.

name: Chutney
description: A spicy and tangy condiment made from a variety of ingredients such as tomatoes, cilantro, and spices.

name: Dahi Chiura
description: A simple and traditional dish made of beaten rice mixed with yogurt, often eaten during festivals.

name: Buff Chhoila
description: A traditional Newari dish made of spiced grilled buffalo meat, often served with beaten rice.

name: Tongba
description: A traditional alcoholic beverage made from fermented millet, typically consumed hot.

name: Dhido
description: A traditional Nepali porridge made from buckwheat or millet flour, usually served with gundruk, achar, and curd.

name: Chiura
description: Beaten rice, often eaten as a snack or with curd and curry.

name: Radish
description: Used in salads, pickles, and curries.

name: Pumpkin
description: Used in various dishes including curries and soups.

name: Okra(Bhindi)
description: A mucilaginous vegetable used in soups, stews, and stir-fries.

name: Bottle Gourd
description: A versatile vegetable used in curries and stews.

name: Rayo ko Saag
description: A leafy green vegetable commonly used in Nepali cuisine.

name: Karkalo Ko Gava
description: The stems of the taro plant, used in various traditional dishes.

name: Cucumber
description: A refreshing vegetable often used in salads and pickles.

name: Bamboo Shoots(Tama)
description: Fermented bamboo shoots used in curries and pickles.

name: Sponge Gourd(Ghiraula)
description: A soft, sponge-like vegetable used in curries and soups.

name: Samosa
description: Deep-fried pastry filled with spiced potatoes, peas, and sometimes meat.

name: Pani Puri
description: Crispy hollow puris filled with spiced water, tamarind chutney, and chickpeas.

name: Aloo Chop
description: Deep-fried potato patties, often served as a snack or appetizer.

name: Sekuwa
description: Marinated and grilled meat, typically served with a side of salad and chutney.

name: Chole Bhature
description: Spicy chickpea curry served with deep-fried bread.

name: Jeri
description: Deep-fried sweet pretzel-shaped snack soaked in sugar syrup.

name: Salmon Fish
description: An oily fish rich in omega-3 fatty acids, typically grilled, baked, or smoked.

name: Trout Fish
description: A cold-water fish with a delicate flavor, often grilled or baked whole.

name: Prawns
description: Large shrimp-like crustaceans, commonly grilled, fried, or used in curries.

name: Crab
description: Crustaceans with tender meat, often steamed, boiled, or used in curries.

name: Oysters
description: Bivalve mollusks with a delicate, briny flavor, often eaten raw or cooked.

name: Octopus
description: Cephalopods with tender meat, often grilled, boiled, or used in salads.

name: Lobster
description: Crustaceans with sweet, tender meat, often boiled or grilled.

name: Papaya
description: Sweet and musky tropical fruit with orange flesh.

name: Guava
description: Tropical fruit with a sweet and tangy flavor.

name: Pineapple
description: Sweet and tangy tropical fruit with yellow flesh.

name: Orange
description: Citrus fruit with a sweet and tangy flavor.

name: Watermelon
description: Juicy and refreshing fruit with red flesh and black seeds.

name: Pomegranate
description: Sweet and tart fruit with juicy seeds.

name: Litchi
description: Sweet and floral tropical fruit with a white, translucent flesh.

name: Kiwi
description: Tangy and sweet fruit with green flesh and black seeds.

name: Grapes
description: Small, sweet or tart berries typically eaten fresh or dried (raisins).

name: Strawberries
description: Sweet and juicy berries with red flesh and seeds on the outside.

name: Plum
description: Sweet and juicy fruit with a smooth skin and stone pit inside.

name: Dragon Fruit
description: Exotic fruit with vibrant pink or yellow skin and white or pink flesh speckled with tiny black seeds.

name: Turnip
description: Root vegetable with a slightly sweet and peppery flavor, used in soups, stews, and roasted dishes.

name: Sisnu (Nettle)
description: Wild leafy green with a slightly bitter taste, used in soups and stews.

name: Niguro (Fiddlehead Ferns)
description: Tender young fern fronds, used in curries and stir-fries.

name: Peach
description: Leaves of the peach tree, used in traditional medicinal and culinary applications.

name: Lettuce
description: Crisp, leafy green often used in salads and as a garnish.

name: Pointed Gourd (Parval)
description: Green vegetable with a mildly sweet taste, used in curries and stews.

name: Drumstick (Moringa) - Sajiwan
description: Long, slender pods with a slightly bitter taste, used in soups and curries.

name: Hyacinth Bean (Hiunde Simi)

name: Amaranth Leaves (Latte ko Saag)

name: Spring Onion

name: Snake Gourd (Chichinda)

name: Jackfruit

name: Chayote (Iscus) Leaves

name: Yam (Rato Tarul)

name: Sweet Potato

name: Roselle (Belchanda)
description: Red, tart fruit used in beverages, jams, and traditional medicines.

name: Soursop (Hanuman Faal)

name: Bel (Wood Apple)

name: Lapsi

name: Amla

name: Mango
description: Sweet, juicy fruit with a tropical flavor, enjoyed fresh or in desserts.

name: Pear (Nashpati)
description: Juicy, bell-shaped fruit with a sweet and slightly grainy texture.

name: Persimmon (HaluwaBed)

name: Cherry

name: Avocado

name: Fig (Anjeer)

name: Malta (Junar)

name: Green Coconut

name: Coconut

name: Sugarcane

name: Honeydew Melon

name: Beetroot

name: Carrot

name: Broccoli

name: Asparagus (Kurilo)

name: Tofu

name: Ginger

name: Chamsur Saag

name: Green Soybeans

name: Cocoyam (Pidali)

name: Green Garlic Leaves

name: Hatch Chilies (Machhey Kursani)

name: Pistachios

name: Dry Coconut

name: Almonds

name: Dates (Khajur)

name: Peanuts

name: Cashew Nuts (Kaju)

name: Walnuts (Okhar)

name: Fox Nuts (Makhana)

name: Yellow Raisins
